This is an open hardware /open software robotics project.


The main idea was to develop a cheap custom robot, based on an embedded Linux plataform, and ROS as robotics standard. 


The robot is based on a Beaglebone but it is almost fully compatible with Beaglebone Black (almost because it was not tested yet).

Software for controlling all aspects of the robot itself are based on the python implementation of ROS Hydro. And it also uses OpenCV for image processing. 

The physical structure can be anything you want, this one is made from Meccano parts. The important thing is that the robot assumes a differencial drive configuration, it means two independent powered wheels.


The low level PCB actually needs to be updated adding a level shifter por ADC voltage, different configuration for battery plug, even a different kind of H-bridge could be used. You are free to suggest or show us different possible improvements.

COSYS-ROS-PKG is a ros package for collaborative wheelchair systems within a smart home setting. Our system could benefit older adults who need assistive powered wheelchairs in their residence to help them with activities of daily living.

The wheelchair is equipped with low cost sensors 

1. Microsoft Kinect

2. Incremental Encoders

3. Inertial Measurement Unit

4. Dynamixel Servo Motors for Pan-Tilt Unit

3. Android Device for User Interface

It runs on embedded linux platform on 

1. Raspberry Pi

2. Intel Edison

3. Arduino

Additional information can be found here:
www.projectcosys.org
